                  <app loc="1">
                     <lem>svasti<surplus>ḥ</surplus></lem>
                     <note>Fleet notes that what looks like a <foreign>visarga</foreign> is probably a punctuation mark, "imperfectly cleared out." He probably refers to the physical cleaning of the plates. In the scanned estampage, the presence of a <foreign>visarga</foreign> seems quite certain.</note>
